sources.title: Arizona Round-Up
sources.description: A standard Monogram matinee western starring Tom Keene. The glitch-free print has good audio and viewable image quality. Directed by Robert Emmett Tansey (as Robert Tansey). Released in 1942. Complete print. CAST NOTE: During the '30s, '40s and '50s Tom Keene (a.k.a. George Duryea & Richard Powers) appeared in dozens of low-budget westerns, either in starring or supporting roles. Today he is probably best known for playing Colonel Edwards in Ed Wood's "Plan 9 from Outer Space," which was his last feature film role.
